    "description": "<p>While driving a <strong>personal vehicle</strong> with an <strong>armor module</strong> enabled, a Pilot does not have access to the normal contents of their <strong>armor slot</strong>. Instead, that slot is considered occupied by the <strong>personal vehicle’s armor module</strong>. If the <strong>personal vehicle</strong> has no armor module enabled, the Pilot can keep using their equipped armor as normal.</p><ul><li><p>As soon as the Pilot stops driving a <strong>personal vehicle</strong> with an enabled <strong>armor module</strong>, they immediately regain access to their normal equipped armor.</p></li><li><p>Armor modules marked with @ICON[martial] are considered to be <strong>martial</strong> armor for the sake of Skills and other effects, and they set the Pilot’s Defense and Magic Defense to <strong>fixed scores</strong> (bonuses from shields and other effects still apply). Note that a Pilot can still equip these modules <strong>even if they normally lack the ability</strong> to equip martial armor.</p></li></ul><blockquote><p><em>For instance, a Pilot with the <strong>Guardian</strong> Class benefits from the <strong>Defensive Mastery </strong>Skill while driving a <strong>personal vehicle</strong> with a <strong>Heavy Plating module</strong> enabled, but they do not benefit from the <strong>Dodge</strong> Skill granted by the <strong>Rogue</strong> Class.</em></p></blockquote><p></p><h2>ARMOR MODULE LIST</h2><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Armor Module</strong></p></td><td><p style=\"width:70px;text-align:center\"><strong>Defense</strong></p></td><td><p style=\"width:90px;text-align:center\"><strong>Magic Defense</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>@UUID[Compendium.projectfu.vehicle-modules.Item.kohdoUC4txAMLWDy]{Flexible Plating}</p></td><td><p style=\"width:70px;text-align:center\">DEX size + 2</p></td><td><p style=\"width:90px;text-align:center\">INS size + 1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>@UUID[Compendium.projectfu.vehicle-modules.Item.TpTXbLUkL3Pu19Cd]{Heavy Plating} @ICON[martial]</p></td><td><p style=\"width:70px;text-align:center\">12</p></td><td><p style=\"width:90px;text-align:center\">8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>@UUID[Compendium.projectfu.vehicle-modules.Item.008QW2xjRc0BT2Az]{Runic Plating} @ICON[martial]</p></td><td><p style=\"width:70px;text-align:center\">10</p></td><td><p style=\"width:90px;text-align:center\">11</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>@UUID[Compendium.projectfu.vehicle-modules.Item.RjB4wyGuxUBc9fgu]{Standard Plating} @ICON[martial]</p></td><td><p style=\"width:70px;text-align:center\">11</p></td><td><p style=\"width:90px;text-align:center\">10</p></td></tr></tbody></table>",
